HEADWORD: phlebotomus
<hw>phlebotomus</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A mild viral disease
transmitted by the bite of the sand fly <spn>Phlebotomus
papatasii</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sandfly fever, pappataci fever.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[Capitalized]</mark> <def>A genus of small
blood-sucking mothlike sand flies.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Phlebotomus</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phlebotomy</ent>⟦br⟧
